name: DescribeQuickActionResult
description: Contains describe metadata information for a quick action.

getactionenumorid().name: getActionEnumOrId
getactionenumorid().description: Returns the unique ID for the action. If the action doesn’t have an ID, its API name is used.

getcanvasapplicationname().name: getCanvasApplicationName
getcanvasapplicationname().description: Returns the name of the Canvas application, if used.

getcolors().name: getColors
getcolors().description: Returns an array of color information. Each color is associated with a theme.

getcontextsobjecttype().name: getContextSobjectType
getcontextsobjecttype().description: Returns the object used for the action. Replaces getsourceSobjectType() in API version 30.0 and later.

getdefaultvalues().name: getDefaultValues
getdefaultvalues().description: Returns the default values for a action.

getflowdevname().name: getFlowDevName
getflowdevname().description: If the custom action invokes a flow, returns the fully qualified name of the flow invoked by the custom action.

getflowrecordidvar().name: getFlowRecordIdVar
getflowrecordidvar().description: If the custom action invokes a flow, returns the input variable that the custom action passes the record’s ID to.

getheight().name: getHeight
getheight().description: Returns the height in pixels of the action pane.

geticonurl().name: getIconUrl
geticonurl().description: Returns the URL of the 32x32 icon used for the action.

geticons().name: getIcons
geticons().description: Returns a list of Schema.DescribeIconResult objects that describe colors used in a tab.

getlayout().name: getLayout
getlayout().description: Returns the layout sections that comprise an action.

getlightningcomponentbundleid().name: getLightningComponentBundleId
getlightningcomponentbundleid().description: If the custom action invokes a Lightning component, returns the ID of the Lightning component bundle to which the component belongs.

getlightningcomponentbundlename().name: getLightningComponentBundleName
getlightningcomponentbundlename().description: If the custom action invokes a Lightning component, returns the name of the Lightning component bundle to which the component belongs.

getlightningcomponentqualifiedname().name: getLightningComponentQualifiedName
getlightningcomponentqualifiedname().description: If the custom action invokes a Lightning component, returns the fully qualified name of the Lightning component invoked by the custom action.

getshowquickactionlcheader().name: getShowQuickActionLcHeader
getshowquickactionlcheader().description: Returns an indication of whether  the Lightning component quick action header and footer are shown.

getshowquickactionvfheader().name: getShowQuickActionVfHeader
getshowquickactionvfheader().description: Returns an indication of whether  the Visualforce quick action header and footer should be shown.

getsourcesobjecttype().name: getSourceSobjectType
getsourcesobjecttype().description: Returns the object type used for the action.

gettargetparentfield().name: getTargetParentField
gettargetparentfield().description: Returns the parent object’s type for the action.

gettargetrecordtypeid().name: getTargetRecordTypeId
gettargetrecordtypeid().description: Returns the record type of the targeted record.

gettargetsobjecttype().name: getTargetSobjectType
gettargetsobjecttype().description: Returns the action’s target object type.

gettype().name: getType
gettype().description: Returns a create or custom Visualforce action.

getvisualforcepagename().name: getVisualforcePageName
getvisualforcepagename().description: If Visualforce is used, returns the name of the associated page for the action.

getvisualforcepageurl().name: getVisualforcePageUrl
getvisualforcepageurl().description: Returns the URL of the Visualforce page associated with the action.

getwidth().name: getWidth
getwidth().description: If a custom action is created, returns the width in pixels of the action pane.
